OL,3,CPaedophile who arranged to rape two
OL,4,Cchildren at hotel jailed
OL,6,FHackett admitted the offences and was
OL,7,Fjailed for seven and a half years with
OL,8,Fan extended four-year licence period.
OL,9,FHe was also handed a Sexual Harm
OL,10,FPrevention Order and ordered to sign
OL,11,Fthe sex offenders register for life.
OL,13,FPC Jodie Norris, who led the
OL,14,Finvestigation, said: "Hackett, who was
OL,15,Falready a registered sex offender when
OL,16,Fhe committed this offence, clearly
OL,17,Fposes a serious danger to children and
OL,18,FI am very pleased that his sentence
OL,19,Freflects that danger.
